    "asOf": "2021-04-29",
    "date": "2021-11-20T20:10:58Z",
    "text": "Drug Price Transparency Act of 2021\n\nThis bill provides statutory authority for the limitation on which type of prescription drug rebates are exempt from federal anti-kickback laws. Specifically, a rebate from a drug manufacturer to a health insurer or pharmacy benefit manager is exempt only if the rebate (1) is disclosed to the consumer at the point of sale, or (2) is a flat fee paid for pharmacy benefit management services."
